window.__QUIZ_DATA__=[{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>1","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"SOUND WAVES : SPEED OF SOUND","question":"The S.I unit of sound energy is","images":[],"options":{"A":"Hz.","B":"cd.","C":"dB.","D":"J."},"answer":"D","explanation":"The SI unit of energy, including sound energy, is the joule (J). Sound energy is a form of mechanical energy that is created when a force causes an object or substance to vibrate \u2014 the energy is transferred through the substance in a wave. Therefore, the correct answer is J.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>2","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"HOOKE\u2019S LAW, YOUNG\u2019S MODULES AND WORK DONE IN SPRINGS AND STRING :","question":"The general definition of elastic modulus is","images":[],"options":{"A":"stressstrain","B":"strainstress","C":"stress x strain","D":"\u221astress/strain"},"answer":"A","explanation":"ElasticModulus=Young'sModulus=Tensile StressTensile strain","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>3","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"FLUID AT REST : PRESSURE IN FLUIDS","question":"The diagram above illustrated a simple barometer. Which distance measures the atmospheric pressure?","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"PQ","B":"QR","C":"RS","D":"QS"},"answer":"B","explanation":"The part which measures the atmospheric pressure is QR.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>4","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"NEWTON\u2019S LAWS OF MOTION : FIRST LAW","question":"The property of a body to remain at rest or to continue in a uniform motion, in a straight line is called","images":[],"options":{"A":"momentum","B":"inertia","C":"impulse","D":"energy"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Inertia is the tendency of a body at rest to remain at rest or a body undergoing uniform motion along a straight line to continue in that state of motion.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>5","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"SIMPLE HARMONIC MOTION : SIMPLE HARMONIC MOTION (S.H.M)","question":"During a training session, two footballers pass a ball repeatedly between each other. The 'to and fro' motion of the ball is not simple harmonic because the   I. acceleration of the ball is not directed towards a fixed point   II. restoring force is not directed towards the centre.  III. acceleration of the ball is not directly proportional to the displacement from a fixed point     Which of the statements above are correct?","images":[],"options":{"A":"I and III only","B":"I and II only","C":"II and III only","D":"I, II and III"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The 'to and fro' motion of the ball is not simple harmonic because all the three statements are correct. In a simple harmonic motion, the acceleration of the object is always directed towards a fixed point (the equilibrium position), the restoring force is always directed towards the centre and the acceleration of the object is directly proportional to its displacement from its equilibrium position.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>6","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"FLUID AT REST : EQUILIBRIUM OF BODIES: ARCHIMEDES\u2019 PRINCIPLE","question":"A dam is able to hold  large quantity of water because its wall is","images":[],"options":{"A":"thickest at the top","B":"thickest at the middle","C":"thickest at the bottom","D":"of the same thickness throughout"},"answer":"C","explanation":"A dam is able to hold large quantity of water because of the fact that it is thickest at the bottom.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>7","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"WORK, ENERGY AND POWER : WORK DONE IN A GRAVITATIONAL FIELD","question":"A body of mass m moving round a circle of radius r with a uniform speed v experiences a centripetal force F. The work done by the centripetal force on it is","images":[],"options":{"A":"Fv.","B":"zero","C":"Fmr","D":"Fr/m"},"answer":"B","explanation":"a = ac {centripetal acceleration)  Fc = mac  The motion starts from A; and ends at A.  The work done = 0","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>8","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"NEWTON\u2019S LAWS OF MOTION : SECOND LAW","question":"A block is acted upon by two horizontal forces as illustrated in the diagram above. The block accelerate at 1.5ms-2. Calculate the mass of the block.","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"6 kg","B":"9 kg","C":"10 kg","D":"15 kg"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Net force on the body = 10N - 1N = 9N  Recall: FN = ma ------------- *  9 = 1.5(m)  m = 6.0kg","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>9","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"FUNDAMENTAL AND DERIVED QUANTITIES AND UNITS : DERIVED QUANTITIES AND UNITS","question":"Which of the following quantities are dimensionally independent?   I. dielectric constant   II. momentum   III. efficiency   IV. refractive index","images":[],"options":{"A":"I and II","B":"II, III and IV","C":"I, II, III and IV","D":"I, III and IV"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Momentum is the only quantity in the option that has a dimension, the remaining quantities in the options are dimensionless.  Momentum = mass \u00d7 velocity  = kgms-1  The dimension of momentum = MLT-1.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>10","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"PROJECTILE MOTION :","question":"A body is projected with an initial velocity u at angle \u03b8 to the horizontal. If Rmax is the maximum range of the projectile, what does the relation  represent u2/Rmax respectively.","images":[],"options":{"A":"The vertical distance covered","B":"Acceleration due to gravity","C":"The horizontal distance covered","D":"The acceleration of the body due to gravity"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The range R of the motion is given as  R=u2sin2\u03b8g  at Rmax, i.e when \u03b8 = 45\u00b0  Rmax=u2sin90\u00b0g  Rmax=u2g  g=u2Rmax------------***  \u2234u2Rmax=accelerationduetogravity","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>11","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"WORK, ENERGY AND POWER : CONCEPT OF ENERGY","question":"An object at rest is said to posses","images":[],"options":{"A":"potential energy","B":"kinetic energy","C":"chemical energy","D":"electrical energy"},"answer":"A","explanation":"An object at rest is said to possess potential energy.    at point A, the body possesses P.E = Wh = mgh","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>12","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"HEAT ENERGY : HEAT TRANSFER","question":"According to Newton's law of cooling, the heat energy lost her unit area of a body depends the   I. Surface area   II. Nature of the surface   III. Temperature of the surface","images":[],"options":{"A":"I and II only","B":"II and IV only","C":"I, II and III","D":"I, II and IV"},"answer":"C","explanation":"According to the Newton's law of cooling.  Heatlostpersecond=dQdt=KS(\u03b8-\u03b8R)-------(1)  S \u2192 Area of the body surface  \u03b8R \u2192 temperature of the surrounding  K \u2192 a constant that depends on the nature of the surface.  Only the temperature of the surface does not fall into the equation.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>13","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"FLUID AT REST : VOLUME, DENSITY AND RELATIVE DENSITY","question":"The graph of density against temperature for water is correctly illustrated by","images":["data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"","B":"","C":"","D":""},"answer":"C","explanation":"Normally, the higher the temperature, the lower the density and vice versa.  But it should be noted between 0\u00b0C and 4\u00b0C water behaves anomalously, i.e it density increases with temperature; from 4\u00b0c and above, it tends to decrease with temperature.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>14","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"PROJECTILE MOTION :","question":"A football is kicked at an angle of 45o to the horizontal over a defence line up with a velocity of 15 ms-5. Calculate the magnitude of horizontal velocity of the ball at its highest point. (Neglect friction, g = 10 ms-2)","images":[],"options":{"A":"0.0 ms-1","B":"5.6  ms-1","C":"10.6  ms-1","D":"15.0  ms-1"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Uy = Usin\u03b8  Ux = Ucos\u03b8  From = v = u + at  since the ball is moving upward from A to B i.e a = -g  v = u - gt  vy = uy - gt  vy = usin\u03b8 - gt ----------- *  vx = ucos\u03b8 --------- **  As the ball goes up, Vy decreases and when it gets to the highest point, Vy = 0.  N.B: Vx (horizontal velocity) is constant through out the motion.  Vx=15cos45\u00b0=15(1&radic;2&nbsp;)=15&radic;2&nbsp;=7.5&radic;2&nbsp;=10.6ms-1","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>15","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"HEAT ENERGY : TEMPERATURE AND ITS MEASUREMENT","question":"The ice point on the absolute scale of temperature is","images":[],"options":{"A":"0 K.","B":"32 K.","C":"100 K","D":"237 K."},"answer":"A","explanation":"The ice point on the absolute scale of temperature, also known as the Kelvin scale, is 0 K. This is the lowest possible temperature, where all thermal motion ceases.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>16","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"HEAT ENERGY : EVAPORATION AND BOILING","question":"Which of the following factors does not increase the rate of evaporation of water in a lake?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Increase in the pressure of the atmosphere","B":"Rise in temperature","C":"Increase in the surface area of the lake","D":"Increase in the speed of wind"},"answer":"A","explanation":"The rate of evaporation increases with   - an increased surface area  - an increased wind speed  - an increased temperature.  N.B: Atmospheric pressure decreases with evaporation rate.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>17","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"SIMPLE HARMONIC MOTION : PERIOD, FREQUENCY AND AMPLITUDE OF A BODY EXECUTING S.H.M","question":"The bob of a simple pendulum takes 8.0 s to complete 10 oscillations. Determine the frequency of oscillation of the bob.","images":[],"options":{"A":"0.80 Hz","B":"1.25 Hz","C":"7.50 Hz","D":"8.00 Hz"},"answer":"B","explanation":"The frequency of oscillation of the bob is the reciprocal of the time taken for one oscillation. Given that the bob takes 8.0 s to complete 10 oscillations, the time for one oscillation is 8.0 s / 10 = 0.8 s. Therefore, the frequency is 1 / 0.8 s = 1.25 Hz.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>18","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"HEAT ENERGY : TEMPERATURE AND ITS MEASUREMENT","question":"The diagram above illustrates the mercury-in-glass the thermometer used for determining the temperature of a room. Use the date on it to determine the room temperature.","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"3.3oC","B":"7.0oC","C":"13.0oC","D":"30.0oC"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Recall:  TcT100=XT-XoX100-X0  X \u2261 Thermometric property like volume, pressure, length (in this case)  Tc100=3cm10cm (We are comparing with the centigrade scale)  Tc = 30\u00b0C","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>19","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"PRODUCTION AND PROPAGATION OF WAVES : FREQUENCY (F), WAVELENGTH(\ud835\udecc), PERIOD (T) AND VELOCITY (V)","question":"Frequency is measured in","images":[],"options":{"A":"metre per second","B":"second","C":"hertz","D":"farad"},"answer":"C","explanation":"The S.I unit of frequency is Hertz.  This was named after Friedrich Hertz, who gave the most acceptable definition of frequency.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>20","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTROMAGNETIC WAVES: : ELECTROMAGNETIC SPECTRUM","question":"Which of the following electromagnetic wave is most energetic?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Radio waves","B":"X-ray","C":"Gamma rays","D":"Ultra-violet rays"},"answer":"C","explanation":"From, E = hf ----------- * {According to Max Planck}  The higher the energy, the higher the frequency and vice versa. So the one with the highest frequency will have the highest energy.    According to the arrange Gamma rays are the most energetic since they have the highest frequency.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>21","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"LIGHT WAVES : DISPERSION OF WHITE LIGHT","question":"Rainbow formation is a natural phenomenon illustrating that white light","images":[],"options":{"A":"splits into three components after rainfall","B":"is dispersed by glass prisms.","C":"splits into its constituent colours before rainfall","D":"is dispersed into its constituent colour by raindrops"},"answer":"D","explanation":"A rainbow is a meterological phenomenon that is caused by reflection, refraction and dispersion of light in water droplets resulting in a spectrum of light appearing in the sky.  &nbsp &nbsp The rainbow formation is basically due to 3 phenomena refractive total internal reflection and dispersion.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>22","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"LIGHT WAVES : APPLICATION OF LENSES IN OPTICAL INSTRUMENTS","question":"The lens illustrated above can best be described as a","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"converging meniscus","B":"plano-convex","C":"diverging meniscus","D":"bi-convex"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Plano-convex lenses are positive spherical lenses having convex surface on one side and flat surface on the other.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>23","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"LIGHT WAVES : REFLECTION OF LIGHT AT CURVED SURFACES","question":"Two plane minors are inclined to each other such that an object between them has 11 images. Determine the angles of inclination","images":[],"options":{"A":"300","B":"450","C":"600C","D":"900C"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Recall: When two plane mirrors are inclined at an angle \u03b8, the number (n) of images formed is given by:  n=360\u03b8-1  11=360\u03b8-1  12=360\u03b8  12\u03b8 = 360  \u03b8 = 30\u00b0","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>24","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"SOUND WAVES : CHARACTERISTICS OF SOUND","question":"The pitch of a note is not affected by","images":[],"options":{"A":"frequency","B":"tension in a vibrating string","C":"mass of a vibrating string","D":"amplitude of sound wave"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Pitch depends on frequency, f  Recall:F=v\u03bb-----------*  For a string,    L=\u03bb2  \u03bb = 2L  \u2234f=V2L;f=12L&radic;T\u03e5&nbsp;  \u03e5=mL\u2192masslength(Tistension)  So automatically, pitch depends of frequency, mass and tension.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>25","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTRIC FIELD : CAPACITANCE, ARRANGEMENT AND APPLICATION","question":"When two flat plate conductors are arranged in such a way that they passes equal and opposite changes separated by a dielectric, they from a/an","images":[],"options":{"A":"electroscope","B":"electrophorus","C":"capacitor","D":"cell"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Diagrammatically, we have:     This description gives a capacitor.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>26","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTROMAGNETIC FIELD : MOTOR-GENERATOR EFFECT","question":"Which electricity device does the diagram above illustrate?","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"a.c. generator","B":"a.c. motor","C":"d.c. generator","D":"d.c. motor"},"answer":"A","explanation":"This is a diagrammatic representation of an A.C generator or alternator.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>27","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"FLUID AT REST : PRESSURE IN FLUIDS","question":"A simple barometer is constructed using a liquid Q1 of density 16.2g/cm3. Calculate the least length of the tube to be used to measure pressure of 1.5 atmospheres.   (Density of mercury = 13.6/cm3)  [atmosphere = 76.0 cm of mercury]","images":[],"options":{"A":"1358 mm","B":"957 mm","C":"760 mm","D":"638 mm"},"answer":"D","explanation":"pressure of mercury = pressure of liquid   P = hpg  hmpmgm = hQpQgQ  7 x 13.6 x 10 = hQ x 16.2 x 10  76x13.6x1016.2x10=hQ    hQ = 63.8cm= 638mm","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>28","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"EQUILIBRIUM OF FORCES : CONDITIONS FOR EQUILIBRIUM OF RIGID BODIES UNDER THE ACTION OF PARALLEL AND NON-PARALLEL FORCES","question":"A bar AB is balanced horizontally on two knife edges as illustrated in the diagram above. Determine the weight of the bar","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"10.0N","B":"20.0N","C":"40.0N","D":"50.0N"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Since the question says it is \"balanced horizontally\", it means it is at equilibrium.  One of the conditions for equilibrium, particularly for a body that is acted upon by a system of parallel forces is that:  Total upward force = Total downward force  20N + 20N = W  40N = W  W = 40N  The weight of the ruler is 40N.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>29","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"LIGHT WAVES : APPLICATION OF LENSES IN OPTICAL INSTRUMENTS","question":"To obtain a virtual, erect and magnified image from a thin converging lens, an object must be placed","images":[],"options":{"A":"between the focus and the lens","B":"at the focus","C":"between the focus and twice the focal length","D":"beyond twice the focal length"},"answer":"A","explanation":"A converging lens is a convex lens.  To obtain a virtual, erect and magnified image the object must be placed between the focal point (F) and the lens     the object must between the focus and the lens.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>30","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"PROPERTIES OF WAVES : SUPERPOSITION","question":"The diagram above represents a transverse travelling wave. Which two points are 1800 out of phase?","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"A and E","B":"B and D","C":"C and F","D":"D and H"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Points    B    and   D   are   out of  phase by 180\u00b0","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>31","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"GRAVITATIONAL FIELD : NEWTON\u2019S LAW OF GRAVITATION","question":"Two objects P and Q of masses 100kg and 20kg respectively are 1.2m apart on a horizontal surface. Calculate the net gravitational force","images":[],"options":{"A":"1.11 x 10-7N towards P","B":"1.11 x 10-7 towards Q","C":"9.26 x 10-8 towards P","D":"9.26 x 10-8 towards Q"},"answer":"D","explanation":"mp = 100kg  mq = 20kg  r = 1.2m  Fg = unknown     FPQ = Force on P due to Q  F=GM1M2r2  =66.67x10-11x100x20(1.2)2   = 9.26 x 10-8   It is towards Q because Q is a lighter object and will move  a bit faster hence the force will act in the direction of Q.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>32","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTROMAGNETIC FIELD : POWER TRANSMISSION AND DISTRIBUTION","question":"The primary of a transformer has 100 turns and its secondary has 200 turns. If the voltage at the primary is 100 V, determine the voltage at the secondary","images":[],"options":{"A":"50 V","B":"100 V","C":"200 V","D":"400 V"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Np = 100  Ns = 200  Vp = 100v  Vs = unknown  N.B: N means number of turns     N \u03b1 V  NpNs=VpVs--------*  Note that we are dealing with a step up transformer here since Np s.  100200=100Vs  Vs = 200V","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>33","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"EQUILIBRIUM OF FORCES : CONDITIONS FOR EQUILIBRIUM OF RIGID BODIES UNDER THE ACTION OF PARALLEL AND NON-PARALLEL FORCES","question":"In the diagram illustrated above, a block of mass M is at rest on a plane inclined at an angle \u03b8 to the horizontal. As \u03b8 increase, the velocity ratio of the plane","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"increases","B":"decreases","C":"remain the same","D":"decreases and later increases"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Recall: For such inclined plane;  V.R=1sin\u03b8  V.R\u03b11\u03b8(becausesin\u03b8increases\u03b8)  So as increases, V.R decreases.  Check for \u03b8 = 30\u00b0, 45\u00b0, 60\u00b0 and 90\u00b0 you will see that V.R decreases as \u03b8 increases.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>34","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"WORK, ENERGY AND POWER : CONCEPT OF ENERGY","question":"When the speed of a car is halved, its kinetic energy is","images":[],"options":{"A":"doubled","B":"quartered","C":"halved","D":"quadrupled"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Recall:  K.E=12mV2  Let the mass be constant.  k.E1k.E2=V12V22  whenthespeedishalved,i.eV2=V12  E1E2=V12V124  E1E2=41  E2=E14  When the speed is halved, the energy is quartered.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>35","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"PRODUCTION AND PROPAGATION OF WAVES : SPEED, FREQUENCY AND WAVELENGTH","question":"A wire of length 400 cm is stretched between two fixed points. When plucked, its fundamental frequency is 150 Hz. Calculate the speed of the wave produced.","images":[],"options":{"A":"250 ms-1","B":"625 ms-1","C":"1200 ms-1","D":"1500 ms-1"},"answer":"C","explanation":"L = \u03bb/2 = 400cm  \u03bb = 800cm  \u03bb = 8m  Recall, V = f\u03bb  V = 150 \u00d7 8  V = 1200ms-1.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>36","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"PRODUCTION AND PROPAGATION OF WAVES : WAVEFORM","question":"The diagram above illustrated a waveform. Determine the number of wavelength in it.","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"4","B":"312","C":"212","D":"2"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Count the number of oscillation  n=212  wavelengthnumber=212  N.B: Number of oscillations = Number of wavelengths","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>37","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTRIC FIELD : RESISTIVITY AND CONDUCTIVITY","question":"A resistor with fixed resistance value is called a","images":[],"options":{"A":"resistance box","B":"standard resistor","C":"shunt","D":"multiplier"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Standard resistor is a resistor with fixed resistance value.  Note that a resistor with variable resistance value is called a rheostat.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>38","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTRIC FIELD : STORAGE OF CHARGES","question":"Which of the following statements is not an advantage of an alkaline accumulator?","images":[],"options":{"A":"The electrolyte does not need attention","B":"It can be recharged","C":"It has low internal resistance","D":"It has a much longer life than lead-acid"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Advantages of Alkaline Accumulators  - Large current can be drawn from them, meaning they have low internal resistance  - They require little attention to be maintained  - They are lighter than the lead-acid accumulators  - It is rechargeable.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>39","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTRIC FIELD : ELECTRIC CIRCUIT","question":"The diagrams above illustrates the wire connections to a three-pin plug. The wires P, Q and R respectively are","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"live, neutral and earth","B":"neutral, earth and live","C":"earth, live and neutral","D":"earth, neutral and live"},"answer":"B","explanation":"From the diagram above, it can be seen that,  P = Neutral  Q = Earth  R = Live","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>40","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTRIC FIELD : CAPACITANCE, ARRANGEMENT AND APPLICATION","question":"Which of the following statements about parallel plate capacitors is/are correct?   I. Capacitance of the capacitor is inversely proportional to the distance between the plates   II. Capacitors can filter a.c. signals from d.c.   III. Capacitors can store changes","images":[],"options":{"A":"I only","B":"I and II only","C":"II and III only","D":"I, II and III"},"answer":"D","explanation":"All I, II and III are correct.  - Capacities store charges (III is correct)  -FromC=A\u03b50d,Iiscorrect  - Capacitors can filter a.c signals from d.c (II is correct)","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>41","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTRIC FIELD : ELECTRIC CIRCUIT","question":"A circuit contains three ammeters A1, A2 and A3 with reading of A2 and A3 shown as indicated in the diagram above. Determine the reading of A1","images":["data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"2 A","B":"3 A","C":"5 A","D":"8 A"},"answer":"B","explanation":"The current that flows from the source is I which is equal to 5A, this same current enters R1, but when it gets to point C, the currents into A1 (which enters R2) and A2 (which enters R3)  A3 = A1 + A2  5A = A1 + 2A  A1 = 3A","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>42","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"MAGNETIC FIELD : CONCEPT OF MAGNETIC FIELD","question":"Which of the following statements about magnetic lines of force is not correct? They","images":[],"options":{"A":"pass through even non-magnetic materials","B":"run from the north pole to the south pole","C":"are in a state of tension and tend to be shorted","D":"intersect one another"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Magnetic lines of force do not intersect each other. Each line of force provides a distinct path for the magnetic field, and no two field lines can intersect each other. If they did, it would mean that at the point of intersection, the magnetic field would have two different directions, which is not possible.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>43","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTROMAGNETIC FIELD : EDDY CURRENTS","question":"In which of the following activities is an induction coil not useful?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Investigation of high voltages","B":"Study of electric discharge","C":"Operation of X-ray tubes","D":"A.C. power transmission"},"answer":"D","explanation":"An induction coil is a type of electrical transformer used to produce high-voltage pulses from a low-voltage direct current (DC) supply. It is not useful in AC power transmission.","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>44","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"SIMPLE A.C. CIRCUITS : IMPEDANCE","question":"In a series R-L-C circuit, R = 10 ohm, Xc = 4F and XL = 9 ohm. The impedance of the circuit is","images":[],"options":{"A":"4.1 ohm","B":"5.0 ohm","C":"10.8 ohm","D":"11.2 ohm"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Diagrammatically, we have     R \u2192 Resistance {opposition to the flow of current in a resistor}  XL \u2192 Inductive reactance {opposition to the flow of current in an inductor}  XC \u2192 Capacitive reactance {opposition to the flow of current in a capacitor}  Z \u2192 Impedance {resultant or effective opposition to the flow of current}  If you are interested in the phasor diagram, here is it,     We are going to use (c) to compute Z     \u2234 z2 = 102 + 52  z2 = 100 + 25  z2 = 125  z = &radic;125&nbsp; = 5&radic;5&nbsp; = 11.2 ohm","marks":"1","difficulty":"3"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>45","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"MAGNETIC FIELD : CONCEPT OF MAGNETIC FIELD","question":"A student uses two compass needles to investigate the magnetic field around a bar magnet. Which of the following diagrams show the correct directions of the needles?","images":["data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,","data:image/png;base64,"],"options":{"A":"","B":"","C":"","D":""},"answer":"B","explanation":"the diagram that shows the correct direction of the needles is:","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>46","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"STRUCTURE OF THE NUCLEUS : RADIOACTIVITY","question":"Which of the following particles may be emitted in a process of natural radioactivity?","images":[],"options":{"A":"\u03b1 - particles and \u03b2 - particles","B":"\u03b1 - particles and X-rays","C":"\u03b2 - particles and X rays","D":"y  - rays and X-rays"},"answer":"A","explanation":"Natural radioactivity is the emission of any of \u03b1 - particle, \u03b2-particles and \u03b3-rays from the nucleus of an unstable atom.","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>47","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"STRUCTURE OF THE ATOM : PHOTOELECTRIC EFFECT","question":"In which of the following situations is photoelectric effect employed?   I. Automatic devices for switching on light at dusk   II. Automatic doors in departmental stores   III. Automatic devices for switching on air conditioners  IV. Automatic voltage stabilization","images":[],"options":{"A":"I, II and IV only","B":"I, III and IV only","C":"III and IV only","D":"I and II only"},"answer":"D","explanation":"The photoelectric effect is the phenomenon where electrons are ejected from a material when light of sufficient frequency shines on it. This principle is employed in automatic devices for switching on light at dusk (I), and automatic doors in departmental stores (II).","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>48","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"ELECTROMAGNETIC WAVES: : ELECTROMAGNETIC SPECTRUM","question":"Which of the following radiations has the longest wavelength?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Gamma ray","B":"Radio wave","C":"Infrared ray","D":"X-ray"},"answer":"B","explanation":"Radio wave has the highest wavelength","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>49","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"STRUCTURE OF THE NUCLEUS : RADIOACTIVITY","question":"In which of the following fields is radioisotopes not used?","images":[],"options":{"A":"Medicine","B":"Oil industry","C":"Agriculture","D":"Weather forecast"},"answer":"D","explanation":"Radioisotopes are used in various fields such as medicine, oil industry, and agriculture for different purposes like diagnosis and treatment of diseases, tracing oil and gas flow, and improving crop varieties respectively. However, they are not used in weather forecasting. Weather forecasting relies on meteorological data and does not involve the use of radioisotopes.","marks":"1","difficulty":"1"},{"id":"objective>Physics>2018>50","subject":"Physics","year":"2018","type":"Objective","topic":"STRUCTURE OF THE NUCLEUS : COMPOSITION OF THE NUCLEUS","question":"A muscle is represented by 7032B   Determine its neutron-proton ratio.","images":[],"options":{"A":"0.5","B":"0.8","C":"1.2","D":"1.5"},"answer":"C","explanation":"Given the atom:  7032B  Note that: 70 = Atomic mass = Number of proton + Number of neutron   and  32 = Atomic number = Number of proton  Recall: Atomic mass = Number of proton + Number of neutron  70 = 32 + Nn  Nn = 38  Neutron-protonratio=3832=1.2","marks":"1","difficulty":"2"}];